ProMED
<promed@usa.healthnet.org>
[This is a strange coincidence. A human case of suspected trypanosomiasis
(probably *not* of African origin) turns up in Sri Lanka last month, & now
suspected cases, of alleged African origin, appear in tigers in Bangladesh.
We wonder what gave the zoo veterinarians the idea of that inherently
unlikely diagnosis? Do they have game animals recently imported from Africa
in the zoo?
And we would still like to hear the final diagnosis from Sri Lanka - Mod.JW
......................................tg/jw

